## 📜 **Historical Timeline of African Americans**

📍 **1619** – First enslaved Africans arrive in Jamestown, Virginia.  
📍 **1776** – Enslaved and free Black people fight in the **American Revolution**.  
📍 **1863** – _Emancipation Proclamation_ → Enslaved people in Confederate states are declared free.  
📍 **1865** – **13th Amendment** abolishes slavery (except in prisons).  
📍 **1868** – **14th Amendment** grants citizenship to formerly enslaved people.  
📍 **1870** – **15th Amendment** gives Black men voting rights.  
📍 **1896** – _Plessy v. Ferguson_ legalizes segregation (**Jim Crow era begins**).  
📍 **1910s-30s** – **Great Migration** → Millions of Black Southerners move North & West.  
📍 **1950s-70s** – **Civil Rights & Black Power Movements** reshape racial justice activism.  
📍 **1980s-90s** – **Hip-Hop & Black Cultural Renaissance** influence global culture.  
📍 **2010s-Present** – **Black Lives Matter Movement** fights systemic racism & police violence.

