### **3️⃣ Civil Rights, Black Power & Social Justice (1950s–1980s)**

- **Civil Rights Movement (1950s–60s)** → Ended legal segregation & expanded voting rights.
- **Black Power Movement (1960s–70s)** → Advocated for self-determination & community control.
- **Mass Incarceration (1980s-Present)** → The "New Jim Crow" targets Black communities.

